{{italic title}}
'''''Hermetic Definitions''''' was a text written in [[Armenian language|Armenian]] about [[Hermeticism|Hermetic]] [[Alchemy]]. It consists of a long list of defined terms on God, the World, heaven, mind and soul, earth, and the elements.<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Vigiliae Christianae|date=December 1985|title=Review|jstor=1583779|volume=39|pages=403–406}}</ref> It is considered of the founding Hermetic texts (The ''Corpus Hermeticum''),<ref>[http://www.granta.demon.co.uk/arsm/jg/corpus.html Corpus Hermeticum<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and was originally titled '''''Definitions of Hermes Trismegistos for Asclepius'''''.<ref>[http://www.gangleri.nl/articles/54/what-are-the-hermetic-texts Gangleri - articles » Blog Archive » What are the Hermetic texts?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Versions can be found online in Greek, Latin and English.<ref>http://gnosis.org/library/hermet.htm</ref>

